# Auth & RLS

## Browser session
- Client uses `supabase.auth.*` with the anon key. Protected UI: `RequireAuth` + route guards that query `getSession` / `getUser`.

## RLS
- All user-owned tables use policies keyed on `auth.uid()` — see `supabase/schema.sql`.
- Never trust a client-supplied `user_id`; derive the user from the session on write paths.

## Profiles & budgets
- Upsert `profiles` after sign-in / callback when you have a `user` object.
- Budget writes: same shape as before; `saveBudget` in `client/src/features/onboarding/lib/saveBudget.ts`.

## Demo / email confirmation
- Seeded user and local demo expect **Confirm email** off for frictionless QA — see README.
